# Root Package (draw, main, app_state)

## AppState (`app_state.odin`)

`AppState` is the single source of truth. All mutable application state lives here. Helper procedures in this file orchestrate cross-package calls (e.g., `commit_color` updates history and slots, `update_harmony` delegates to `color.compute_harmony`).

When adding new features, add fields to `AppState` — never introduce module-level variables.

## Main Loop (`main.odin`)

The main loop follows a strict order each frame:

1. `defer free_all(context.temp_allocator)` — first line in the loop
2. Handle special modes (eyedropper) with early `continue`
3. Handle input (file drops, export panel, picker, sliders, hex, keyboard shortcuts, palette)
4. Rebuild textures if underlying values changed
5. Update derived state (FG/BG slots)
6. `BeginDrawing` / `EndDrawing` block with draw calls

Never mix input handling into draw procedures and never draw outside the BeginDrawing/EndDrawing block.

## Drawing (`draw.odin`)

- Every draw procedure receives `app: ^AppState` and `mouse: rl.Vector2`
- Draw procedures are named `draw_<section>`: `draw_header`, `draw_picker`, `draw_harmony_section`
- Some draw procedures handle inline interaction (dropdowns, toggles) and return flags — this is acceptable for tightly coupled draw+interact widgets, but prefer delegating to `ui.draw_*` where possible
- Use `ui.MARGIN`, `ui.RIGHT_X`, etc. for positioning — never hardcode pixel values in draw code
- Use `ui.TEXT_CLR`, `ui.ACCENT`, etc. for colors — never hardcode color literals
